| Giant         | Spider           |
| HoTK          | All runes + BC4  |




Dead Cells Side – How This Actually Works
This is the heart of the project.

A. Communication Model (Locked Choice)
✔ File-based bridge

Dead Cells script:
* Reads ap_items.json
* Writes ap_locations.json

External AP client:
* Talks to Archipelago server
* Updates these files




B. Script Responsibilities (main.hx)
The Dead Cells script will:
On game start / level load
* Read ap_items.json
* For each unprocessed item:
    - Apply effect
    - Mark as processed (local state)

On boss death:
* Detect which boss died
* Write location ID to ap_locations.json
* Ensure one-time send per save

C. Applying Items (Concrete)
Runes
Set appropriate progression flags
Same flags the vanilla game uses
Persist across runs
Boss Cells
Increase BC count
Unlock difficulties automatically
No Collector interaction needed

D. Persistence
We must store:
Which AP items were already applied
Which locations were already checked
Options:
File in mod folder (simplest)
CDB flags (riskier across updates)

🟢 Recommendation:
v0 = simple JSON state file


6️⃣ AP Side – Client + World
AP World

Defines:

Locations = bosses

Items = runes + BCs

Logic rules

AP Client (Bridge)

Responsibilities:

Connect to AP server

When item received:

Append to ap_items.json

When location read:

Send check to server

This can be:

Python

Minimal UI

Reusable later